          "active": true,
          "timeZone": "Pacific/Pitcairn"
        },
        "body": "Hi [~zhuqi]\r\n\r\nThanks. Are you suggesting to let parameter \\{{yarn.nodemanager.remote-app-log-dir}} support multiple dirs, and use e.g round-robin policy to select dirs? If this is the case, will this break something? Such as history server, timeline-server or log CLI etc, I assume some of these components need to read logs from this location. Please elaborate, thanks.",
