            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
          },
          "displayName": "Tao Yang",
          "active": true,
          "timeZone": "Asia/Shanghai"
        },
        "body": "Hi, [~zhuqi].\r\nJust noticed this issue. \r\nThe staging directories used for submission should be managed by application frameworks instead of YARN, requirements are different for frameworks and they should maintain the staging directories themselves, as far as I know, Flink and Spark both can cleanup the staging directories after app totally terminate.\r\nFor log-aggregation directories, there is a cleanup thread in JobHistoryServer, the TTL of these directories can be configured by \"yarn.log-aggregation.retain-seconds\", -1 by default means cleanup disabled, for example, you can set 604800 to retain them for only a week to avoid overflowing the quota.",
        "updateAuthor": {
